.PP
This function does the actual audio data conversion, after the application has called \fBSDL_BuildAudioCVT()\fP to prepare the conversion information and then filled in the buffer details\&.
.PP
Once the application has initialized the \fCcvt\fP structure using \fBSDL_BuildAudioCVT()\fP, allocated an audio buffer and filled it with audio data in the source format, this function will convert the buffer, in-place, to the desired format\&.
.PP
The data conversion may go through several passes; any given pass may possibly temporarily increase the size of the data\&. For example, SDL might expand 16-bit data to 32 bits before resampling to a lower frequency, shrinking the data size after having grown it briefly\&. Since the supplied buffer will be both the source and destination, converting as necessary in-place, the application must allocate a buffer that will fully contain the data during its largest conversion pass\&. After \fBSDL_BuildAudioCVT()\fP returns, the application should set the \fCcvt->len\fP field to the size, in bytes, of the source data, and allocate a buffer that is \fCcvt->len * cvt->len_mult\fP bytes long for the \fCbuf\fP field\&.
.PP
